Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Symptom: {{primarySymptom}}
Recent Service: {{recentService}}
Aftermarket Mods: {{aftermarketMods}}

Provide a mechanical engine diagnosis procedure including:
1. Compression test procedure and expected values
2. Leak-down test if compression is low
3. Timing chain/belt inspection procedure
4. Bearing noise isolation technique
5. Oil pressure test procedure and spec

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Symptom: {{primarySymptom}}
Waveform uploaded: {{engineWaveform}}

Analyze the engine sensor / electronic fault:
1. Interpret the uploaded waveform pattern (if provided)
2. Expected CKP/CMP waveform patterns for this vehicle
3. Ignition coil primary circuit expected voltage patterns: 12V supply → 300-400V inductive kick
4. Injector pulse-width analysis at idle vs. loaded
5. Sensor reference voltage checks (5V ref, ground integrity)
6. PCM driver circuit tests

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Symptom: {{primarySymptom}}

Diagnose fuel/air system issues:
1. Fuel pressure test — key-on engine-off (KOEO) and running pressure
2. Fuel trim analysis (STFT/LTFT interpretation)
3. MAF/MAP sensor validation
4. Vacuum leak detection procedure (smoke test)
5. Throttle body and IAC valve inspection
6. EVAP system check if purge-related codes present

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
CAN Waveform uploaded: {{canbusWaveform}}

Diagnose High-Speed CAN bus issues:
1. Expected HS-CAN waveform: CAN-H 2.5→3.5V, CAN-L 2.5→1.5V (differential ~2V)
2. Bus termination resistance check: should measure ~60Ω between CAN-H and CAN-L (two 120Ω resistors in parallel)
3. Module-by-module isolation procedure (unplug one at a time, check bus recovery)
4. Common HS-CAN failure modes: shorted module, corroded connector, chafed wiring harness
5. Interpret the uploaded waveform — identify stuck dominant, stuck recessive, noise, or ringing
6. DLC pin identification: Pin 6 = CAN-H, Pin 14 = CAN-L

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
CAN Waveform uploaded: {{canbusWaveform}}

Diagnose Low-Speed CAN / LIN bus issues:
1. Expected LS-CAN single-wire waveform (0V recessive, ~5V dominant on some platforms, or fault-tolerant CAN at ~2.2V / ~2.8V)
2. LIN bus single-master protocol: ~12V recessive, ~0V dominant, 19.2 kbaud typical
3. Gateway module function and how LS-CAN connects to HS-CAN
4. Common body module failures: BCM, seat module, mirror module, HVAC control
5. Parasitic draw relationship — LS-CAN module staying awake causes battery drain

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
CAN Waveform uploaded: {{canbusWaveform}}
Scan Screenshot: {{scanScreenshot}}

Perform full CAN/LIN network diagnosis:
1. Identify all U-codes and map them to specific buses (HS-CAN, MS-CAN, LS-CAN, LIN)
2. Gateway module health check
3. Power and ground integrity at DLC and major module connectors
4. Bus topology map for this vehicle platform
5. Step-by-step half-split isolation procedure
6. Check for aftermarket devices on the OBD-II port that may disrupt bus communication

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Electrical Waveform: {{electricalWaveform}}

Diagnose starting and charging system:
1. Battery test: CCA rating vs measured, state of charge, internal resistance
2. Starter current draw test: typical 150-250A for 4-cyl, 200-350A for V8
3. Cranking voltage drop test: battery terminal → starter (should be <0.5V)
4. Alternator output test: 13.8-14.4V at idle, AC ripple <0.5V peak-to-peak
5. Alternator diode pattern — analyze the uploaded waveform for open/shorted diodes
6. Ground integrity tests at engine-to-body and battery-to-body straps

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Draw Measurement: {{electricalWaveform}}

Diagnose parasitic battery drain:
1. Acceptable draw: typically <50mA after modules sleep (30-60 min timeout)
2. Milliamp clamp method vs fuse-pull method
3. Module sleep timer procedure — close all doors, wait for BCM/GEM timeout
4. Fuse-by-fuse isolation: pull fuses one at a time while monitoring current
5. Common culprits: aftermarket radio, OBD-II dongle, trunk light, seat module, Bluetooth module
6. Current waveform interpretation: periodic wake-up spikes are normal (network management), constant >80mA is abnormal

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Symptom: {{primarySymptom}}

Diagnose lighting and accessory circuit faults:
1. Power distribution diagram approach — trace from fuse box to load
2. Voltage drop testing: supply side and ground side (<0.1V per connection)
3. Relay testing: coil resistance, contact resistance, click test
4. BCM-controlled lighting: verify BCM commands via scan tool
5. LED and HID headlight module diagnostics
6. Multifunction switch and combination switch testing

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Symptom: {{primarySymptom}}

Diagnose manual transmission / clutch issues:
1. Clutch pedal feel and engagement point assessment
2. Hydraulic clutch: master cylinder and slave cylinder inspection, fluid check
3. Synchro ring wear test: double-clutch vs difficult engagement
4. Input shaft bearing noise: goes away when clutch is depressed
5. Shift linkage adjustment and cable inspection
6. Flywheel inspection: dual-mass flywheel (DMF) rattle test

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Symptom: {{primarySymptom}}

Diagnose mechanical brake issues:
1. Pad and rotor measurement: minimum thickness specs for this vehicle
2. Rotor lateral runout measurement (max typically 0.002")
3. Brake noise diagnosis: squeal (glazing/vibration), grinding (metal-to-metal), clunk (loose caliper)
4. Brake pull diagnosis: caliper piston retraction, hose restriction (infrared temp comparison)
5. Parking brake adjustment and cable inspection
6. Brake drum: shoe measurement, drum max diameter, self-adjuster function

Vehicle: {{vehicleInfo}}
OBD Codes: {{obdCodes}}
Symptom: {{primarySymptom}}

Diagnose HVAC airflow and actuator issues:
1. Blower motor: test with direct 12V, check resistor/module, speed control module
2. Blower motor resistor testing: typical resistance values per speed position
3. Blend door actuator: motor test, position feedback, calibration procedure
4. Mode door actuator: verify defrost/floor/panel door movement
5. Recirculation door: check for cabin filter restriction
6. Evaporator drain tube: check for blockage causing water intrusion or musty odor
